# Agent Guide

This repository is an experiment monorepo: `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`.

## Default approach

- Treat `experiments/<name>/` as the primary work unit.
- Start in the target experiment directory before reading broad repo docs.
- Use root docs only when the task changes repo-wide conventions or spans multiple experiments.
- Treat `scaffolds/` as the harness source of truth when creating a new experiment or reconciling style drift.

## Experiment contract

Every experiment should stay self-contained and generally include:

```text
experiments/<name>/
|-- pyproject.toml
|-- README.md
|-- train.py
|-- autoresearch.sh
|-- autoresearch.md
`-- data/
    `-- sources.yaml
```

Detailed section order, helper names, artifact names, and profile guidance live under `scaffolds/`.

## Rules

- Each experiment should remain understandable without reading unrelated experiments.
- Prefer experiment-local code while the repo is still small.
- Avoid introducing shared dependencies unless multiple experiments already need the same code.
- `train.py` must support `--eval-only`.
- `train.py` should support `--dry-run` when local data and prompt formatting can be validated without runtime credentials.
- `train.py` must print `METRIC <name>=<value>` lines.
- `uv run train.py --eval-only --eval-data <full_eval_path>` is the canonical benchmark confirmation entrypoint; `autoresearch.sh` is the wrapper that `pi-autoresearch` should use for the current practical line.
- Reusable experiment-template changes should land in `scaffolds/` before they spread across multiple experiments.

## Root files

- `README.md` explains the repo shape.
- `experiments/README.md` summarizes the shared experiment contract and index.
- `scaffolds/README.md` points to the canonical experiment scaffold.
- `.env.example` is the shared checked-in live env template for the repo; experiments may keep local `.env` files, but not their own checked-in `.env.example` copies.

## Skills

When this repo also carries Codex skills, the common ones are:

- `$project-harness-bootstrap` - maintain the repo-level harness
- `$new-experiment` - add a concrete experiment directory from `scaffolds/`
- `$new-experiment-plus` - upgrade a canonical scaffold into a research-ready harness
- `$helper-contract-alignment` - reconcile shared helper contracts across experiments and scaffolds
- `$mint-api` - API reference for training code
